cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.HC

The paper proposes a method based on deep learning for the detection of premature ventricular contractions (PVC) using a densely connected convolutional neural network with spatial pyramid pooling layer. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the method involves image processing techniques. The paper also involves the use of multiple databases for training and testing, which suggests the possibility of using neural networks for transfer learning, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a likely sub-category. Additionally, the use of deep learning techniques for medical diagnosis and analysis suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) sub-categories.
